form_title.ms_form_title_llm_v1: EXAMINER'S REPORT OF TESTIMONY OF WITNESS

full_text: UNITED STATES DEPARTMENT OF JUSTICE Immigration and Naturalization Service EXAMINER'S REPORT OF TESTIMONY OF WITNESS (Section 341 of the Immigration and Nationality Act) File No. A20 181 518 Date: 5-15-74 DISTRICT DIRECTOR OR OFFICER IN CHARGE I certify that on 5-15-74 at Houston, Texas (Date) (City, State, and, if foreign, Country) I examined Nathan Dwoskin under oath, and on the basis thereof, I made the (Name of Witness) following findings: 1. Witness resides at Apt. 102, Townhouse West, 4610 Beechnut St., Houston, Texas about 2. Witness was born on 8-28-1891 at Bobrouisk, State of Minsk, Russia 3. Witness is the uncle of (State relationship, friend, etc.) Joseph Young and did - (Applicant's name) identify the photograph sub- mitted with the application as that of the applicant. Witness is younger brother of applicant mother. 4. Witness has - personal knowledge of the relationship between the applicant and (no) Isadore Young , having been acquainted with the appli- (Person(s) through whom citizenship is claimed) cant since about 1901 (Date) and the person(s) through whom citizenship is claimed since about 1900 (Date) I further certify that I examined this witness regarding all of the essential facts alleged in the application and contained in the record of the case and that no discrepancies or inconsisten- cies were disclosed, except: --No material discrepancies, but see notes on other side of this page- (Officer's signature) Form N-341 Gen. Attorney (Nationality) HOU (Rev. 5-20-65) (Officer's title)
